  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this prospective, randomized study was to compare the clinical and
      radiographic results and the prevalence of osteolysis of the cementless total hip
      arthroplasty with an alumina-on-alumina bearings one side and alumina-on-highly cross-linked
      polyethylene bearings on the other side in the young and active patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
